default3.3.7
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultItem 5: Edge Hill to Wavertree. A section of disused land north of the current railway would allow two tracks of HS2 to be constructed as far as Wavertree Technology Park Station.
default&#xa0;
default3.3.8
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultItem 6: The Olive Mo
defaultunt Cutting. The historic cutting was originally built for four tracks but is now used by two. The unused south side of the cutting could accommodate one track of HS2. The second track would run in tunnel to the north. The route would continue in tunnel to
default Bowring Park where it reaches open land.
default&#xa0;
default3.3.9
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultItem 7: The Liverpool Loop Railway. The disused but intact Liverpool Loop Line could form an alternative route for HS2 southwards. I
defaultt was built for four tracks and so would easily accommodate the two track of HS2. A route to open country is available at Gateacre.
